         <lb n="c56-0110_main_2"/>This advice, although good, was utterly <w ana="start"/>inna<lb n="c56-0110_main_3"/>plicable<w ana="end"/> to my case; I should have been <lb n="c56-0110_main_4"/>the first to hide my grief and console <lb n="c56-0110_main_5"/>my friends if remorse had not mingled its <lb n="c56-0110_main_6"/>bitterness with my other sensations. Now <lb n="c56-0110_main_7"/>I could only answer my father with a <lb n="c56-0110_main_8"/>look of despair and endeavour to <lb n="c56-0110_main_9"/>hide myself from his view. About this <lb n="c56-0110_main_10"/>time <del rend="strikethrough">also</del> we retired to our house at <lb n="c56-0110_main_11"/>Belrive. This <del rend="strikethrough">chal</del> change was very <lb n="c56-0110_main_12"/>agreable to me in particular. The <lb n="c56-0110_main_13"/>shutting of the gates of the town regularly <lb n="c56-0110_main_14"/>at ten o'clock and the impossibility of <lb n="c56-0110_main_15"/>
